Installation & Running Instructions
1. Prerequisites
Before installing the project, ensure your system has the following:
PHP 8.2 or higher.
Composer (for PHP dependencies)
Node.js & npm (for frontend assets)
MySQL
XAMPP / LAMP installed for running local server

2. Project Setup

Step 1: Clone the Project
Clone the Laravel project to your local environment:
Step 2: Install PHP Dependencies
Install all PHP dependencies including the vendor folder via Composer:
Step 3: Install Node Modules
Install frontend dependencies required for Laravel Breeze and other assets:
Step 4: Configure Environment
Copy the .env.example file to .env:
2. Generate an application key:
2. Running the Project
Start your XAMPP / LAMP server (Apache + MySQL).
Start Laravel development server:

